ata-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532919\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104uzv1665702678968.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uzv1665702678968.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uzv1665702678968.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"uzv1665702678968\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define Component Operations of a Signature\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Operations are the interfaces to components. Every component has a set of\n      custom-defined operations. You can define these interfaces using the Signature\n      Editor.</p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"uzv1665702678968__context_w5500ab1b5b1_w5501ab1b5_w5502ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"uzv1665702678968__topic_d34055e1_d34056e1_d34057e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uzv1665702678968__p_d34061e1_d34062e1_d34063e1\">To define an operation signature:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"uzv1665702678968__li_d17453e1_d17454e1_d17455e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"uzv1665702678968__p_d34064e1_d34065e1_d34066e1\">From the Signature Editor, click the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">&gt;&gt;</span> button adjacent to the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Details of\n                  Operation</span> field. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">The Define Operation form is displayed.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"uzv1665702678968__li_d17456e1_d17457e1_d17458e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">New</span> button.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"uzv1665702678968__li_d17459e1_d17460e1_d17461e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"uzv1665702678968__p_d34067e1_d34068e1_d34069e1\">Enter an <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Operation</span>\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jrq1665702585385.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jrq1665702585385.html\" title=\"Name of the development object, which uniquely identifies it.\">Name</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mvb1665702679041.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mvb1665702679041.html\" title=\"Specify whether the component instance runs synchronously or asynchronously.\">Communication Default</a>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">For non-Uniface implementations, this name is mapped to the literal name.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"uzv1665702678968__li_d17462e1_d17463e1_d17464e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"uzv1665702678968__p_d34070e1_d34071e1_d34072e1\">Define the other properties of the\n               operation.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For foreign implementations, specify a case-sensitive name for the operation in\n                  the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Literal Name</span> field. Uniface maps the operation name to\n                  the literal name.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uzv1665702678968__p_d34073e1_d34074e1_d34075e1\">For C implementations only, if you create a new\n                  operation in the Signature Editor, Uniface generates the default name\n                     <span class=\"keyword\">ComponentName_OperationName</span> to ensure that it is unique. You\n                  will likely need to change this to reflect the actual operation/method name of the\n                  component.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"uzv1665702678968__li_d17465e1_d17466e1_d17467e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To delete an operation, in the Define Operation form, select the operation you want to delete and click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Delete</span>.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"uzv1665702678968__result_w5503ab1b5b5_w5504ab1b5_w5505ab1\">\n<div class=\"sectiondiv postreq\" id=\"uzv1665702678968__topic_d34076e1_d34077e1_d34078e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uzv1665702678968__p_d34079e1_d34080e1_d34081e1\">Define the operation parameters. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wez1665702679109.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wez1665702679109.html\" title=\"Parameters enable you to pass information in and out of operations. For Uniface components, you can define parameters by entering ProcScript in the appropriate operation or trigger. When integrating non-Uniface components, you can define parameters in the component signature using the Signature Editor.\">Define Operation Parameters in a Signature</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vrb1707739762002.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Operations</a><p>Operations are ProcScript modules that are analogous to methods in other programming languages; they perform specific actions and can be activated by other ProcScript modules, and even by non-Uniface components.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532919\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532919\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define Component Operations of a Signature Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define Component Operations of a Signature Operations are the interfaces to components. Every component has a set of custom-defined operations. You can define these interfaces using the Signature Editor. To define an operation signature: From the Signature Editor, click the >> button adjacent to the Details of Operation field. The Define Operation form is displayed. Click New button. Enter an Operation Name and Communication Default . For non-Uniface implementations, this name is mapped to the literal name. Define the other properties of the operation. For foreign implementations, specify a case-sensitive name for the operation in the Literal Name field. Uniface maps the operation name to the literal name. For C implementations only, if you create a new operation in the Signature Editor, Uniface generates the default name ComponentName_OperationName to ensure that it is unique. You will likely need to change this to reflect the actual operation/method name of the component. To delete an operation, in the Define Operation form, select the operation you want to delete and click Delete . Define the operation parameters. For more information, see Define Operation Parameters in a Signature . Related Links Operations Operations are ProcScript modules that are analogous to methods in other programming languages; they perform specific actions and can be activated by other ProcScript modules, and even by non-Uniface components. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}